<br>
The age 8 for LDS is given in a book of scripture called the Doctrine and Covenants chapter 68:25.27  Before a child or any person for that matter is baptized LDS.  They have an interview with either the bishop or the missionaries who are teaching them (converts).  They must demonstrate a knowlege of what they are doing and be able to answer basic questions about our beliefs.  This is to assure that they are making the decision on their own.  <br>
<br>
When I was a missionary the oldest person we taught and baptized was a sweet little old grandma at the great age of 82.  So 8 isnt the only age.<br>
