<br>
While it's true that before the age of 8 (or around there depending on intellectual maturity) children don't understand abstract concepts like justice, eternity, god, etc. I wouldn't say that turning 8 or even 9 makes you ready to select something as important as religion (or no religion as the case may be). Atheists don't baptize children, but I still can't imaging having a conversation with my dd in a year and a half concerning matters of belief, cognition, ethics, epistomology, the nature of the universe etc. <br>
<br>
Maybe high school is better, but I have to side with JWs on this (though I have not seen them speak here) that you have to be at least a teen to understand and choose this stuff independently. Any 8 year old is going to do what mom and dad say and worship what mom and dad do--especially after a healthy dose of unopposed or challenged indoctrination in the form of Sunday school or catechism or whatever.<br>
<br>
